<h1>Final Essay Instructions</h1>

<p>PHIL 375 Philosophy of Literature</p>

<p>The final essay is worth 25% of your final grade. It is due on June 21 at 3pm sharp.</p>

<p>How to submit: Submit your final essay on UBC Canvas. There is a dropbox on the course website. Only PDF files are acceptable. If you use Microsoft Word or Open Office, use the "Export" feature to export to pdf. Do NOT use spaces or special characters (except under_score) in the file name. Use as your naming convention <tt>Final_Essay_StudentNumber_FirstName_LastName.pdf</tt>, for example <tt>Final_Essay_73513516_Matthew_Solesbee.pdf</tt><p>. If for some reason you must submit your paper in hardcopy, you must do so with a reason why it is in hardcopy on June 21 during class time in person.</p>

<p>How to format: The length requirement for this paper is &quot;six pages,&quot; where &quot;six pages&quot; means that the length of the paper must be at least six pages and at most seven pages. Use 1.5 line spacing and a font between 11pt and 12pt (incl.). There must also be reasonable margins (use your program's defaults) for the marginal comments of the grader.</p>

<p>How to write: The final essay is different from the first essay. It is an academic paper in which you address a philosophical question based on the readings and the topics we discussed in class. The essay will be marked on content (clarity of presentation, strength of argument, relevance of thesis) and form (spelling, grammar, presentation in print). I recommend this web page to give you a sense of what's important when you write a philosophy paper:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.jimpryor.net/teaching/guidelines/writing.html">http://www.jimpryor.net/teaching/guidelines/writing.html</a></p>

<p>It is important that you choose a topic that your grader has evidence that you are not recycling a paper for a different course, i.e. your paper topic must be sufficiently linked to the course material to provide such evidence.</p>

<p>Here is a key for problems in essays that occur so frequently that I have assigned them numbers for easy reference.</p>

